name: The LAST EVER WestJet Boeing 767 Flight - Takeoff from Calgary Airport
description:
After 5 years of having the 767 in their fleet, WestJet has officially retired its fourth and last aircraft.

C-FOGT, Tail 673, departed Calgary this morning for the very last time for Lake City, Florida to join the other three aircraft at their new life with Amazon Prime Air.

I definitely feel an attachment to these planes, having caught the delivery flights of all four back when they first arrived in Calgary, and they'll be missed! By WestJet maintenance and customer service though, perhaps not so much.

So long, 767!
